<TITLE> Bush: Letting Iran have nuclear arms 'unforgivable' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jerusalem,May 15 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US President George W Bush will tell Israel's parliament on Thursday that letting Iran acquire nuclear weapons would be an "unforgivable betrayal of future generations". "America stands with you in firmly opposing Iran's nuclear weapons ambitions," Bush will tell Israeli lawmakers on the second day of his visit to the Jewish state, according to an advance copy of his speech to be delivered later in the day
